data.title: The Place to Go for Fish & Chips
data.text: The food is very tasty and always fresh. Best Fish & Chips I've had since I moved to the area over a decade ago.

data.title: Food is great....service needs improvement
data.text: Definitely one of the best fish and chips in Elk Grove, but if i have to pull out my wallet to refill on the sodas it leaves me with a bad taste.Add the cost of a refillable soda to the price... as far as i know this is the only place that charged to refill...

data.title: Fish & Chips Time!
data.text: The best fish & chips in town. Must try this.  They always seem to have the fresh fish.  Restaurant is not that big but the fish & chips is very very good.

data.title: Great fish and chips
data.text: Ocean has really good food, excellent fish.  Not a great place to eat i--the place is hot and cluttered, but food to go is great.

data.title: Delicious food
data.text: We stopped here after my father-in-law wanted some catfish for dinner. I ordered the fish & calamari with chips for dinner. I loved it. The mushrooms were a side I added which were incredible! The restaurant itself is outdated but that doesn't affect the taste of the food. I recommend it. My entire family was pleased. We will definitely return here in the future.

data.title: Best zucchini and onion rings!
data.text: My mother in law is 90 and is super picky about food as she rarely if EVER eats out.  But the ONE place she likes to go for "fast food" is Ocean Fish!  All she wants are the onion rings!  Always so tasty!  Fish is great onion rings are the best and my fav is the fried zucchini!  If you want fish and chips there is no better place!  yummy yummy!!

data.title: Decent food, neutral reception
data.text: I was at an all-day seminar at the library, and when we took a 30 minutes lunch break, Ocean FIsh and Chips was the only source of food in sight. When I walked in a little after 12, I was the only customer. I felt a bit rushed to decide by the guy at the counter, and when I asked if there was anything smallish, he gestured to the top of the menu. I chose the single piece of fish with fries. The drink question was also pretty vague - there were several stacks of cups on the counter and a soda machine in the room. I asked what the choices were and he gestured again to the cups, no indication of prices that I could find on the menu. Fish was fresh and tender, chips could've been hotter and crispier, but maybe it was just that I ate my fish before starting in on the chips. Soda refills were 50 cents. Food took a little longer than I would've liked to come out, but at least that means they made it fresh for my order. By the time I finished eating, more than half of the tables were full.

data.title: Authentic Fish and Chips
data.text: If you want to eat some of the best fish and chips that you have ever had then you have to try Ocean Fish & Chips. I have gone to fancier places and ordered fish & chips and nothing comes close to this. The batter is not heavy and they use Alaskan Pollock and it just awesome.
